Date: Wed, 4 Feb 2026 02:33:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/8] feat(memory): add auto-retrieval layer for automatic
 memory injection

This adds a new feature that automatically retrieves relevant memories
based on the incoming message and injects them into the system prompt
before each agent turn.

Key changes:
- New src/memory/auto-retrieval.ts module with:
  - retrieveRelevantMemories() - semantic search on current message
  - formatRetrievedMemories() - formats results for system prompt
  - resolveAutoRetrievalConfig() - config resolution with defaults
  - Smart skip logic for commands, heartbeats, short messages

- Config schema (agents.defaults.memorySearch.autoRetrieval):
  - enabled: boolean (default: false until explicitly enabled)
  - maxTokens: number (default: 800)
  - maxResults: number (default: 5)
  - minScore: number (default: 0.25)

- System prompt integration:
  - New 'autoRetrievedMemory' param flows through prompt builders
  - Injected as '## Recalled Memories' section before Project Context

- Agent runner hook:
  - Calls auto-retrieval before buildEmbeddedSystemPrompt
  - Graceful degradation if retrieval fails
  - Only runs for 'full' prompt mode (not subagents)

The goal: Memory should come to me, not just be available if I look.
